CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 17, 1954, pg. 1, reads: "Pirate Stars - Quite a bit of attention was focused on these stars at Forbes Field Tuesday afternoon when the Pittsburgh Pirates opened the 1954 baseball season against the Philadelphia Phillies. The players, Curt Roberts, left, and Frank Thomas are slated for big things with the Bucs this season. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball players Curtis "Curt" Roberts holding glove, and Frank Thomas, leaning against dugout fence at Forbes Field
